    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-03-20T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-03-20T14:00:00-05:00" n="14"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d14">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/3–2052:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 14<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France (<persName corresp="#p_BONSALPW1"
                            type="from">Bonsal</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-03-20T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 20, 1952—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5748. Eyes only <persName corresp="#p_PERKINSGW1">Perkins</persName> from
                        <persName corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName>. <gloss
                        target="#t_MSAE1">MSA/E</gloss> is proposing in eyes only cable to <persName
                        corresp="#p_HARRIMANWA1">Harriman</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_DRAPERWHJ1">Draper</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_KENNEYWJ1"
                        >Kenney</persName> and you<note n="1" xml:id="d14fn1">This is a reference to
                        telegram <gloss target="#t_Repto1">Repto</gloss> 1321 from Paris, Mar. 20,
                            <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>.</note> that <persName
                        corresp="#p_HARRIMANWA1">Harriman</persName> ask the Secy to send personal
                    message to <persName corresp="#p_EDENA1">Eden</persName> re UK attitude toward
                        <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> in hope modifying UK views prior to
                    ministerial meeting March 27.<note n="2" xml:id="d14fn2">For a general summary
                        and appraisal of the <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> Ministerial
                        Meeting, Mar. 27–29, see <ref target="#d26">Document 26</ref>.</note> It
                    seems to me that current desire to minimize role and reduce effectiveness of
                        <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> is fundamentally an error, contrary to
                    your own position but so far as we know the position of all other members are
                    peculiarly unfortunate at this early stage, attempting to develop constructive
                    relationship <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> with <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss>. I recognize multiplicity of request for Secy’s direct
                    communication with <persName corresp="#p_EDENA1">Eden</persName> but believe
                    importance of this issue justifies such action in his case and hope that he will
                    support the proposal.<note n="3" xml:id="d14fn3">For the text of <persName
                            corresp="#p_ACHESOND1">Acheson</persName>’s letter to <persName
                            corresp="#p_EDENA1">Eden</persName>, see <ref target="#d18">Document
                            18</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BONSALPW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bonsal</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
